---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Hero from "../components/Hero.astro";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Arma Gym">
  <main>
    <Hero
      callToAction="Bulk & Cut"
      buttonText="Start journey"
      companyName="Arma Gym"
    />
    <section class="py-12">
      <div class="flex flex-col justify-center gap-16 max-w-6xl px-5 mx-auto">
        <div class="flex">
          <div>
            <h1 class="text-white text-5xl italic yellowText pb-8">
              Bulking and Cutting
            </h1>
            <p class="text-white">
              Bulking and cutting are two fundamental phases in bodybuilding.
              Bulking involves consuming more calories than needed to gain
              weight and build muscle through resistance training. Cutting, on
              the other hand, requires eating fewer calories than burned to
              reduce fat while maintaining muscle mass.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex">
            <Image
              src={"/images/bulk-cut.webp"}
              alt="bulk"
              width={600}
              height={400}
              class="rounded-xl"
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h1 class="text-white text-4xl italic yellowText pb-8">
            Bulking Phase
          </h1>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-10">
            <li class="text-white">
              <p>
                <strong>Set Your Goal:</strong> Aim to eat 250-500 calories above
                your maintenance level. Use apps like MacroFactor to track calories.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li class="text-white">
              <p>
                <strong>Track Your Protein Intake:</strong> Consume 1.8-2.2g of protein
                per kg of body weight. Opt for lean sources like chicken, beef, fish,
                eggs, and cottage cheese.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li class="text-white">
              <p>
                <strong>Increase Carbs:</strong> Carbs provide energy. Include sources
                like sweet potatoes, rice, pasta, and oats. Eat more carbs pre-workout
                for better performance.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li class="text-white">
              <p>
                <strong>Include Healthy Fats:</strong> Eat fats from olive oil, avocados,
                nuts, and fatty fish.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li class="text-white">
              <p>
                <strong>Training:</strong> Focus on progressive overload. Train at
                least 4-6 times per week and allow recovery days when needed.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li class="text-white">
              <p>
                <strong>Track Your Progress:</strong> Monitor weight, body measurements,
                and personal records. Use body fat percentage assessments available
                at most gyms.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li class="text-white">
              <p>
                <strong>Stay Consistent:</strong> Stick to your meal plan and training
                routine for best results.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h1 class="text-white text-4xl italic yellowText pb-8">
            Cutting Phase
          </h1>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-10">
            <li class="text-white">
              <p>
                <strong>Set Your Goal:</strong> Reduce calorie intake by 250-500
                below maintenance while tracking calories with apps like MacroFactor.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li class="text-white">
              <p>
                <strong>Track Your Protein Intake:</strong> Maintain 1.8-2.2g of
                protein per kg of body weight to preserve muscle mass.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li class="text-white">
              <p>
                <strong>Cut Carbs:</strong> Reduce but donâ€™t eliminate carbs. Focus
                on complex carbs like vegetables and whole grains.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li class="text-white">
              <p>
                <strong>Include Healthy Fats:</strong> Continue consuming healthy
                fats from sources like olive oil, avocados, and nuts.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li class="text-white">
              <p>
                <strong>Training & Cardio:</strong> Incorporate 20-30 minutes of
                cardio post-workout. Consider walking over running to prevent knee
                injuries, or try HIIT workouts.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li class="text-white">
              <p>
                <strong>Stay Hydrated:</strong> Drink enough water to aid fat loss
                and prevent dehydration.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li class="text-white">
              <p>
                <strong>Track Your Progress:</strong> Monitor weight and body composition
                regularly.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li class="text-white">
              <p>
                <strong>Stay Consistent:</strong> Just like bulking, consistency
                in diet and training is key to cutting success.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h1 class="text-white text-4xl italic yellowText pb-8">
            Influencers for Healthy Meals
          </h1>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-10">
            <li class="text-white"><p>Joseph Abell</p></li>
            <li class="text-white"><p>Noel Deyzel</p></li>
            <li class="text-white"><p>Ethan Chlebowski</p></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
